<br>
For one, the game was programmed in the beginning to allow corpse camping bind rushing ect ect.  These are actions that are NOT hardcoded against and there are no rules to stop them (in fact, the rules encourage them).<br>
<br>
Zone plugging makes the everquest system believe that upon zoning, you are an NPC.  NPC's CANNOT zone (not 98% of them anyway) and are not made to zone.  So when the game realizes that you are an NPC, it IMMEDIATELY stops the zoning process.  This is an exploit.  You are fooling the server into believing that you are doing something that you are not.  Similar to a speed hack.<br>
<br>
Having a higher player take you to 20% and then having a lower level finish you off is also an exploit, but on a much lower scale.  The game's mechanics on Sullon Zek are set up so when a higher level kills a target, he does not earn the reward that a lower level would earn.  And it SHOULD be that way.<br>
<br>
But having a higher level do most of the damage, and then the lower level finishes you off is NOT going along with the game mechanics (or the Vision(TM) if you will).  The game is programmed so higher level players do NOT earn a reward from hurting lower levels.  When a higher level does the most damage, and then a lower level kills (especially in my situation, where these two were traveling together, and were there for the purpose of griefing) is an exploit of the game mechanics.<br>
<br>
If the game is not meant to work like that, and you get around it, you ARE performing an exploit.<br>
<br>
Care to make a counter Grimjaw?  Or will you just ramble mindlessly about how Zone Plugging is such a great tactic because you can do it and because it is not currently punishable?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
