<br>
<br>
Yes...there are no GM-implemented rules, at least where gameplay is concerned.  I came here because there would be &lt;b&gt;player-enforced&lt;/b&gt; rules.  These are never set in stone, but always changing, always developing, always adapting to suit the current need.  On this server, they've given us the freedom, and the means, to govern ourselves, for the most part.<br>
<br>
One way or another, we all have expectations, we all have our own &quot;vision [TM]&quot; of how the system should be.  Whatever the majority of the society agrees upon is the set of &quot;rules&quot; that will be implemented...given that they have the determination to enforce them.<br>
<br>
<br>
This isn't anarchy.  Whether we like it or not, we have an online society here, and every society has rules, even if they are unwritten.<br>
<br>
If you want no rules, no consequences, and no societal patterns, go play quake...cause that's not what this game is about...<br>
